# Mobile-first design (Designer)

Every HTML/CSS change in the Designer project must work on mobile, tablet, and desktop.

## XOLogic context

- Dashboard sections are raw HTML fragments (no `<html>`, `<head>`, or `<body>`).
- The live site viewport is handled by XOLogic; local preview uses `preview.html`.

## Requirements

- Use responsive layouts (`flex`, `grid`, `max-width: 100%`) — avoid fixed widths that overflow small screens.
- Add or update `@media` rules when changing header, footer, or nav styles.
- Touch targets: buttons and links should be at least ~44px tap area where possible.
- Images: use `max-width: 100%; height: auto;` in CSS or inline styles.
- Never use broad selectors like `nav { display: none }` — scope to header nav (e.g. `.sb-nav`).

## Breakpoints in this project

| Breakpoint | Behavior |
|---|---|
| ≤1023px | Hamburger menu; `.sb-nav` hidden; header search moves below logo |
| ≤768px | Footer 2-column grid; tighter typography |
| ≤480px | Footer single column |

## Before finishing

- Check layout at ~375px (phone) and ~768px (tablet).
- Test with `preview.html` or `footer-preview.html` via Live Server.
